21/08/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Former Belgrade public prosecutor Rade Terzic, who was arrested on July 20th for alleged ties to the Zemun Clan crime organisation, will remain in custody, the court decided on Monday (August 20th). Court spokesperson Maja Kovacevic-Tomic announced Terzic's detention would be extended two more months at the request of Investigative Judge Dragan Lazarevic. (RTS, Beta, B92 - 20/08/07)
